    {
        "sha": "2dbfc93ab18135762bcf86977dc9ff07e56d9521",
        "author": "Burak Yigit Kaya",
        "email": "byk@sentry.io",
        "date": "2021-03-09T22:38:36Z",
        "message": "upgrade(redis-py): Allow using redis-py@3.4.1 (#46)\n\n`redis-py@3.4.1` has some important concurrency fixes around pool management and doesn't have any breaking changes. That said `3.4.0` has a bug that might potentially be breaking. So this change relaxes the version requirement but excludes the unsafe `3.4.0` version.\r\n\r\nSee the relevant changes from 3.3.11 to 3.4.1: https://github.com/andymccurdy/redis-py/blob/1a41cfd95a53a95b078084d8627be6b6fba3bb71/CHANGES#L59-L106\r\n\r\nNeeded to unblock getsentry/sentry#24235",
        "url": "https://github.com/getsentry/rb/commit/2dbfc93ab18135762bcf86977dc9ff07e56d9521"
    },
